<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The <code>autocorrect</code> attribute controls whether the browser or operating system automatically corrects text as the user types. When enabled, the system silently replaces what it believes are typos with dictionary words — helpful for prose, but destructive for technical content, codes, or identifiers.</p>
<p><strong>Applies to:</strong> <a href="/docs/elements/native/input/"><code>&lt;input&gt;</code></a> (text types), <a href="/docs/elements/native/textarea/"><code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code></a>, and any element with <a href="/docs/attributes/contenteditable/"><code>contenteditable</code></a></p>

