<h2>When to Disable Autocorrect</h2>
<p>Autocorrect is designed for natural language. It actively harms input accuracy when the field expects non-dictionary content:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Usernames and handles:</strong> <code>xKoder99</code> gets corrected to <code>Coder</code></li>
  <li><strong>Product codes and SKUs:</strong> <code>WX-4829</code> gets broken by insertion of spaces or corrections</li>
  <li><strong>Technical terms:</strong> Programming keywords, CSS selectors, shell commands</li>
  <li><strong>URLs and paths:</strong> File paths and API endpoints contain non-word segments</li>
  <li><strong>Abbreviations:</strong> Domain-specific abbreviations are not in the system dictionary</li>
  <li><strong>Invite codes and tokens:</strong> Random alphanumeric strings that must be entered exactly</li>
</ul>

